						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Vīrapāṇḍya, 4+4 = A.D. 955.</p>						

						<p>Gift of 25 sheep for a lamp to the temple by Kiḻavaṉ Aruḷāḻi of Tiruchchuḻiyal for the merit of his son. A shepherd, called Kuḻuvāṇai Pūti of Peruñchennilakkuḍi in Paruttikkuḍi-nāḍu took the sheep in lease <hi rend="italic">(aḍai)</hi> for the supply of ghee.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XIV, No. 80.]</p>						

						</summary>
